<title>USA: Americas Growth Fund sued by investors.</title>
<headline>Americas Growth Fund sued by investors.</headline>
<dateline>MIAMI 1996-12-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Americas Growth Fund Inc said on Friday an investor group that says it owns 10 percent of the company filed a shareholders' lawsuit.</p>
<p>The suit alleges breach of fiduciary duty by the company for ending a proposed merger with Advanced Electronic Support Products Inc on November 8.</p>
<p>The group consists of Kevin King, Herbert Hill -- as general partner of Double H Investment Co and Bargelt Investments -- Bonnie Hayes and Ronald Hayes. It seeks unspecified damages.</p>
<p>The company said it did not know whether the group owned 10 percent of Americas Growth Fund stock.</p>
<p>Americas Growth Fund said it would fight the suit.</p>
